The Views Bootstrap module adds styles to Views to output the results of a view as several common Twitter Bootstrap components.
The Bootstrap accordion displays content in collapsible panels (see documentation).
The Bootstrap carousel displays content as a slideshow (see documentation).
The Bootstrap dropdown style displays a list of links in a drop-down menu format (see documentation).
The Bootstrap grid displays content in a responsive, mobile first fluid grid (see documentation).
The Bootstrap list group displays content in an unordered list with list group classes (see documentation).
The Bootstrap media object displays content with an image item lead with heading and text (see documentation).
The Bootstrap panels displays content in a box with optional header and footer elements (see documentation).
The Bootstrap table style adds default Bootstrap table classes and optional classes (see documentation).
The Bootstrap tabs displays content with tab titles linked to dynamically displayed content (see documentation).
The Bootstrap thumbnails extends the grid display with the thumbnail component to showcase linked images (see documentation).
The amount of time to delay between automatically cycling an item. If false, carousel will not automatically cycle.
The carousel should cycle continuously or have hard stops.
The class to provide on the list element itself.
The class to provide on the wrapper, outside the list.

The number of columns to include in the carousel.
